TY  - JOUR
AU  - Yang, Liyan
AU  - Zhu, Haoxiang
T1  - Strategic Trading When Central Bank Intervention Is Predictable
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/12/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/raab011
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 11
IS  - 4
SP  - 735
EP  - 761
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - Market prices are noisy signals of economic fundamentals. In a two-period model, we show that if the central bank uses market prices as guidance for intervention, large strategic investors who benefit from high prices would depress market prices to induce a market-supportive intervention. Stronger anticipated interventions lead to deeper price depressions preintervention and sharper price reversals post-intervention. The central bank intervention harms strategic investors even though it is the investors who tried to mislead the central bank. The model predicts a V-shaped price pattern around central bank interventions, consistent with recent evidence. (JEL G14, G18)
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/raab011
ER  - 



